      <hedline>
        <hl1>Stolen Sidewalk</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jameson D Garrick letter deplores incursions into Bryant Park, and disruption affecting surrounding sidewalks</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Paradise Lost, Again,'' by Fred Kent (Op-Ed, Sept. 16):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Paradise Lost, Again,'' by Fred Kent (Op-Ed, Sept. 16):</p>
        <p>While I wholeheartedly agree with Mr. Kent's assertion that private enterprise like the 7th on Sixth fashion show shunts lunchgoers, sun-seekers and short-cutters from Bryant Park, I would point out another, more insidious effect of such enterprise: the takeover of sidewalk space along 40th Street and Sixth Avenue by moving trucks and machinery that force pedestrians off the sidewalk and into a single-file line.</p>
        <p>JAMESON D. GARRICK  Darien, Conn., Sept. 17, 2000</p>
      </block>
